column4: ?? Removing any system startup links for /etc/init.d/startup ...
depends..... what was the service exactly?
i wanted to remove startup.sh (from all folders) to put it in a higher one
but then i wrote only startup instead of startup.sh
a script you made by yourself?
yes! startup.sh - but i wrote startup
its no problem.. the /etc/rcN.d links dont keep the .sh extension  you can recreate it with higher numbers to make it run later.
but normally then there is a list from which rcN.d folders the programm is removed...
do you think nothing happend? because startup.sh is still in the rcN.d-folders
did it say where it removed from once it said, removing system scripts.... ?
i haven't a startup in /etc/init.d only a startup.sh - there is only standing:
Removing any system startup links for /etc/init.d/startup ...
it didnt do anthing then ;) dont worry.
